{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d80819a7-75f6-42fd-b4b2-7bff3bbee768","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName); // bonus: verify details\n}\n```\n\n**Why switch?**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws, masking bugs (e.g., the constructor could throw instead of `CreateUser`)\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` pinpoints the exact call and lets you inspect the exception","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a9cfe0ee-afed-422a-ae8d-39fa5e89286f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question - no need to search the codebase.","outputTokens":241,"requestId":"4814:7DDD1:81BD12:95AC4B:69FBEA37"},"id":"9ed6e74a-29d2-44d7-804e-18ef1d3c69bf","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:26:21.559Z","parentId":"46209fed-3e0d-4735-8951-b3f3fd9f4f7e"}
